                            <comment id="14471609" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 24 Aug 2011 13:54:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed code tags&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471673" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 24 Aug 2011 13:56:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;actually I think adding &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; Timestamp plus(Timestamp self, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; days) {
        Calendar calendar = (Calendar) Calendar.getInstance().clone();
        calendar.setTime(self);
        calendar.add(Calendar.DAY_OF_YEAR, days);
        Timestamp ts = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Timestamp(calendar.getTime().getTime());
        ts.setNanos(self).getNanos());
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; ts;
    }&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;is a better way than an instanceof check in the method&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471714" author="driscoll" created="Wed, 24 Aug 2011 15:45:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a matter of taste, but since there&apos;s already a separate method for java.sql.Date, I&apos;m inclined to agree with you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
